>
> &quot;Not really.&quot;
> &quot;Umm, no it doesn&#x27;t.  It simply shows that both Pre Made Groups and Random Solo can all use Voice Chat to enhance their Communication.&quot;
> &quot;Then perhaps Solo Players should start behaving differently... you know, behaving like a Team.  Instead of 5 Individuals that find themselves on the same side of the Rift.  Perhaps the Solo Players should decide to put more focus on each other instead of simply caring about themselves?&quot;
> &quot;Which is the point.  Stop playing like you are Solo.  You have four other Team Mates.  Start using them, start working with them.  Play like a freaking Team.  Learn to work together.  But then, this has ALWAYS been true.&quot;
> 
> &quot;And yet there you are, on the Rift... with a TEAM of Five.  It&#x27;s up to you to decide to work like a team or not to.  It really is THAT simply.  Just like a game of Pick Up Basketball... you either decide to work together, or you fail.  Of course, same is true for an Organized Team that refuses to work together... they Fail.  So whether Solo or Pre Made, the moral of the story is Play As A Team.  Work Together.&quot;
> 
> &quot;Basically, all  you are doing is making excuses to not work together within a Team Dynamic.  Then wondering why a Team Game isn&#x27;t working out for you.&quot;

Except I'm not there with a "team" of five.

I'm there with a "team" of 4, and me. Or a "team" of 3, one other person, and me.

Calling a cow a duck won't make it lay eggs.

Being thrown in with four other strangers encourages far more across-the-board teamplay than being thrown in with a premade group.
